85.6	Hippopotamus	Hippopotamus	The hippopotamus , or hippo, from the ancient Greek for "river horse" (), is a large, mostly herbivorous mammal in sub-Saharan Africa, and one of only two extant species in the family Hippopotamidae (the other is the Pygmy Hippopotamus.) After the elephant and rhinoceros, the hippopotamus is the third largest land mammal and the heaviest extant artiodactyl.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/Hippo_pod_edit.jpg/250px-Hippo_pod_edit.jpg
